sentences: Brigitte Rolland (born 8 October 1964) is a Canadian violinist.
In 1988 she won the Prix d'Europe and was placed second in the London Philharmonic Orchestra Competition.
She began studying the violin at the age of 5 with Maurice Onderet, and from 1971-1980 was a pupil of Mildred Goodman.
In 1981 she entered McGill University where she was a student of Mauricio Fuks.
From 1983-1987 she studied at the Royal College of Music in London under Rodney Friend, and was awarded an associate diploma.
